article.description: St. Bonaventure nips Davidson at the buzzer, 62-61
article.headline: St. Bonaventure nips Davidson at the buzzer, 62-61
article.linkText: St. Bonaventure nips Davidson at the buzzer, 62-61
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Marcus Posley drove the length of the floor and nailed a jumper at the buzzer to lift St. Bonaventure to a 62-61 Atlantic-10 win over Davidson Wednesday night. St. Bonaventure took the lead on a pair of free throws by Dion Wright with four minutes left and nursed it until Peyton Aldridge drilled a 3-pointer off an assist by Brian Sullivan with :06 left for a 61-60 lead. It was the first meeting between the schools as A-10 rivals and the win gave St. Bonaventure coach Mark Schmidt his 200th career victory, snapping a two-game losing skid. Posley finished with 19 points to lead the Bonnies (12-8, 5-4 A-10). Youssou Ndoye finished with 16 points, 12 rebounds and four blocks, including a key block on Jordan Barham at the basket with :35 left. Sullivan finished with 17 points to lead Davidson (14-6, 5-4).
